The paper focuses on designing a light-weight and efficient ConvNet for video recognition tasks, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed methods also involve reducing the computation complexity of convolutions, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions improving the performance of compressed models, which could be related to neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
